deck: Charlie Mudd is the brother of Bill Mudd and 50% of the group known as the Mud Brothers. Alongside his brother he aids the Goon in combating the undead army of the Zombie Priest.
description:
Origin

Charlie Mudd is the brother of Bill Mudd, together they make up the duo known as the Mud Brothers. Originally working as thugs for hire, they changed their ways after being beaten in a fight by The Goon. From that point onward they aided the Goon in his fight against the Zombie Priest in order to defend Lonely Street.

Creation

Charlie Mudd was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

Drawing On Your Nightmares

Charlie and his brother, Bill, were introduced within this short story. Hired by a mobster known as Salvatore, they were sent to collect a debt owed by Spider. However; when he and his brother arrived at Norton's Pub they were misdirected by Spider himself, who told them that Goon was the man they were looking for. Thus began a brawl between the Goon and the Mud Brothers that resulted in a friendship between both brothers and the Goon. Deciding to stick around with the Goon (much due to his local influence) Charlie and his brother betrayed Salvatore and beat him up in the name of the Goon.

The Goon Volume Three

Alongside his brother, Bill, he aided the Goon in fighting waves and waves of zombies from the Zombie Priests undead army. Due to betrayal from one of Goon's pals, Merle, both Charlie and Bill were attacked by allies of the Zombie Priest, resulting in the near death of Charlie and the death of Bill. This event caused Charlie's mind to snap, resulting in him carrying around a stump that looks slightly like the head of his brother and talking to it like it's actually his brother. Despite his fragile mental state, he still comes to the aid of The Goon when called upon.

The Goon: Occasion of Revenge

Spending his days in the swamps near Lonely Street, Charlie is called upon by Franky to help the Goon face his new foes, all led by The Arab. Charlie's brute strength aids in the fight against these new adversaries, allowing "Team Goon" to successfully defend Lonely Street. Charlie was also assigned the task of escorting a high ranking mafia official named Rory to a safe-house, a task he completed with ease.

The Goon: Once Upon A Hard Time

Charlie is called upon to help Spider after Goon rips one of his arms off in a fit of rage; to which Charlie asks why Goon didn't have him rip the limb off of Spider, considering it's what Goon pays Charlie to do. He also appears after Goon has defeated The Arab as a member of the goodbye party.

Skills and Abilities

What he lacks in mental stability and intelligence he makes up for in brute strength. Charlie Mudd's unique physiology grants him a low level of superhuman strength.

deck: Former boxer, now a strongarm serving The Goon.
description:
Origin

His father, Senator Slocomb, left his mother Elaine before he was born. Angry, his mother was always badmouthing his father. His mother died when he was still young. In the orphange, he learned how to box. He quickly rose through the ranks, earning the nickname Kid Gargantuan. Fighting Bull Brugonski, who cheated with loaded gloves, Kid's left eye socket was shattered, leaving him partially blinded. His boxing career over, he got an offer from The Goon to work for him. As a token of good will, The Goon shattered Bull Brugonski's hand with a hammer.

Major Story Arcs

Occasion of Revenge

Tasked with bodyguarding Rory Slocomb, the son of Senator Slocomb, the Kid Gargantuan was told by Ramona that Rory was his halfbrother. Discovering that Rory needed protection because he was a rapist, Kid Gargantuan shot Rory. The Goon was then forced to shoot Kid Gargantuan because he was now a liability.
name: Kid Gargantuan

deck: A devious and talented Decepticon chemist, Oil Slick specializes in weaponized compounds such as the Reverse Evolution virus and Cosmic Rust. He has little to no qualms about testing his chemical weapons on his enemies as well as his allies.
description:
Creation

At Botcon 2008, it was revealed that Oil Slick was an original design by Eric Siebenaler that was never intended to be in the Transformers Animated TV show, but upon finding out about it, the animation crew said they would've worked him in had they been told about it. Oil Slick therefore wound up getting a story in Transformers Animated: The Arrival #3. He also had an animation model made by Irineo Maramba, and made an appearance in episode 27 of the series as part of Strika's team.

Oil Slick's somewhat odd four-wheeled cycle design is borrowed from the Dodge Tomahawk concept motorcycle, implying he can go very fast in his vehicle mode.

deck: Merle is a redneck simpleton at first glance; however, he is also a werewolf and can transform at will.
description:
Origin

While it is unknown how or when Merle became a werewolf, it is known that he is an on/off ally of The Goon.

Creation

Merle was created by Eric Powell and made his first appearance in The Goon #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume One

After The Goon's bounty is raised to a whopping $50,000.00 he becomes a target for many friend and foe alike, including Merle. Thinking he can overpower The Goon, Merle transforms into his wolf form and attacks The Goon from behind; however, he is quickly beaten and scolded for attacking a man from behind. Later on, when The Goon is captured by the Zombie Priest and the G-Men, Merle is recruited by Franky as part of a team to rescue him.

The Goon Volume Two

Merle attends a Christmas party with The Goon & Franky and winds up helping them find several missing children.

The Goon Volume Three

As the undead army of the Zombie Priest begins to grow in numbers, Merle is seen aiding the Goon. Alongside several others such as Dr. Alloy, Bruno, and the Mud Brothers, Merle helps rescue the Buzzard from the Zombie Priest. While Merle proves to be a valuable ally to the Goon he eventually betrays him in an event that results in the death of Bill Mudd. This leads to his own death at the hands of the Goon via torture.

Powers & Abilities

Merle is a seemingly average man (with below average intelligence) but gains a slight strength and size boost by transforming into a large werewolf.
name: Merle

deck: The right hand man of the Zombie Priest; Lazlo seems to hate his position and wishes he could escape his life of servitude.
description:
Origin

Lazlo used to go town to town alongside the Zombie Priest during the early days of American settlement in the west. Together they'd use magic to scam the townspeople, kill them, and then raise them as members of their undead army. At some point in time Lazlo was killed but was brought back to life by the Zombie Priest to continue aiding him in his quest for domination.

Creation

Lazlo was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume 1

Lazlo is first seen informing the Zombie Priest about the losses they've suffered due to The Goon. He then brings a chimpanzee that the Zombie Priest had wanted and straps it down to a table. Lazlo then learns that his boss, the Zombie Priest, wishes to turn it into a Giant Zombie Chimp and finds the idea to be crazy; however, realizing he isn't in the place to make remarks he just goes along with the idea. Later on, when The Goon arrives at the Zombie's hidden base Lazlo releases the Giant Zombie Chimp to distract The Goon, allowing him and the priest to escape.

Lazlo is seen again with the Zombie Priest after the chimp failed to defeat The Goon, causing the Zombie Priest to scream and yell while Lazlo is busy wishing he could kill himself and end his servitude. When The G-Men arrive to make a deal with the Zombie Priest, Lazlo is instructed to eat their faces, a task he refuses.

Eventually, when The G-Men capture The Goon, Lazlo is seen once more. He survives the battle following The Goon's escape and is ordered by the Zombie Priest to gather the dead bodies of The G-Men in order for future experiments.

The Goon Volume 2

With the escape of The Goon, Lazlo takes more of a backseat in the Zombie Priest's army. He attempts to ambush The Goon & Franky with aid from Milo, however, when the Buzzard interferes he finds himself bested. Buzzard also manages to gnaw off several of Lazlo's undead fingers. After this failure he returned to the Zombie Priest to plan a new assault.

The Goon Volume 3

Lazlo works alongside other henchmen such as Houstus Grave and the Mongoloid Twins. Due to repeated failures he feels pressured to abandon the cause, and does so when Labrazio is reanimated by The Arab. He meets his final death after Franky unloads on his cranium with a sub-machine gun, causing it to explode.

Powers & Abilities

As a zombie Lazlo was able to function with the loss of vital organs; however, he could still be killed if he sustained severe head trauma.
name: Lazlo

deck: Houstus Grave is a faithful servant to the Zombie Priest. His main job is collecting corpses for the Zombie Priest to reanimate in order to help his army grow.
description:
Origin

Houstus Grave was originally a good man who had fallen under hard times. A lack of income led to a life of poverty for he and his wife, Mary, who was expecting two children. Fortunately (or unfortunately depending on perspective) Houstus met the man known as the Zombie Priest who offered Houstus a steady income in return for dead bodies. While Houstus did his duties he became ill with a strange form of leprosy that spread to his wife who now hated him. On her deathbed she cursed Houstus and gave birth to two deformed children, the Mongoloid Twins, then died leaving Houstus alone with his children to continue down the path he had chosen for himself.

Creation

Houstus Grave was created by Eric Powell for 'The Goon' comic series.

Major Story Arcs

The Goon Volume Three

Houstus Grave and his two deformed children are tasked with locating more dead bodies for the Zombie Priest. During their travels they come in conflict with The Goon and Franky who prevent them from achieving their goal. Eventually Houstus is given another chance to prove himself by obtaining the Mother Corpse, a task he succeeds in. Houstus eventually abandons the Zombie Priest as was sick of dealing with his increasing madness, his fate after this is unknown.
name: Houstus Grave

deck: Electrical based villain of the Flash, Overload was born with a sort of chronic pain resulting from electronic buzzing that gave him electricity based powers as well as technophobia. Aims to create a sort of blackout, such as the one that occurred in Forever Evil, in order to take the pain away.
description: The man known as Overload was born screaming and never stopped according to his mother due to what doctors called "chronic pain". As it turns out, this pain was the result of electronic signals and buzzing that in addition to hurting him charged him up with electrical power. When the Crime Syndicate of America caused a blackout during the events of Forever Evil, Overload's pain went away but quickly returned once things returned to normal. Overload vowed to eliminate the buzzing and resents not being born in a time where buzzing wouldn't have been a problem. Because of his adversity to electronics and signals, Overload travels in horse and carriage with a horse named Alastair.
